verses.text_plain: Dead flies cause the ointment of the apothecary to send forth a stinking savour: so doth a little folly him that is in reputation for wisdom and honour.
verses.verse_html:
1Dead flies cause the ointment of the apothecary to send forth a stinking savour: so doth a little folly him that is in reputation for wisdom and honour. ▼
▼ Dead…: Heb. Flies of death

footnotes.body_html: ▼ Dead…: Heb. Flies of death

verses.text_plain: A wise man’s heart is at his right hand; but a fool’s heart at his left.
verses.verse_html: 2A wise man’s heart is at his right hand; but a fool’s heart at his left.

verses.text_plain: Yea also, when he that is a fool walketh by the way, his wisdom faileth him, and he saith to every one that he is a fool.
verses.verse_html:
3Yea also, when he that is a fool walketh by the way, his wisdom faileth him, and he saith to every one that he is a fool. ▼
▼ his…: Heb. his heart

tokens.text: Yea also, when he that is a fool

footnotes.body_html: ▼ his…: Heb. his heart

verses.text_plain: If the spirit of the ruler rise up against thee, leave not thy place; for yielding pacifieth great offences.
verses.verse_html: 4If the spirit of the ruler rise up against thee, leave not thy place; for yielding pacifieth great offences.

verses.text_plain: There is an evil which I have seen under the sun, as an error which proceedeth from the ruler:
verses.verse_html:
5There is an evil which I have seen under the sun, as an error which proceedeth from the ruler: ▼
▼ from: Heb. from before

footnotes.body_html: ▼ from: Heb. from before

verses.text_plain: Folly is set in great dignity, and the rich sit in low place.
verses.verse_html:
6Folly is set in great dignity, and the rich sit in low place. ▼
▼ in great…: Heb. in great heights

footnotes.body_text: ▼ in great…: Heb. in great heights
footnotes.body_html: ▼ in great…: Heb. in great heights

verses.text_plain: I have seen servants upon horses, and princes walking as servants upon the earth.
verses.verse_html: 7I have seen servants upon horses, and princes walking as servants upon the earth.

verses.text_plain: He that diggeth a pit shall fall into it; and whoso breaketh an hedge, a serpent shall bite him.
verses.verse_html: 8He that diggeth a pit shall fall into it; and whoso breaketh an hedge, a serpent shall bite him.

verses.text_plain: Whoso removeth stones shall be hurt therewith; and he that cleaveth wood shall be endangered thereby.
verses.verse_html: 9Whoso removeth stones shall be hurt therewith; and he that cleaveth wood shall be endangered thereby.

verses.text_plain: If the iron be blunt, and he do not whet the edge, then must he put to more strength: but wisdom is profitable to direct.
verses.verse_html: 10If the iron be blunt, and he do not whet the edge, then must he put to more strength: but wisdom is profitable to direct.

verses.text_plain: Surely the serpent will bite without enchantment; and a babbler is no better.
verses.verse_html:
11Surely the serpent will bite without enchantment; and a babbler is no better. ▼
▼ a babbler: Heb. the master of the tongue

footnotes.body_text: ▼ a babbler: Heb. the master of the tongue
footnotes.body_html: ▼ a babbler: Heb. the master of the tongue

verses.text_plain: The words of a wise man’s mouth are gracious; but the lips of a fool will swallow up himself.
verses.verse_html:
12The words of a wise man’s mouth are gracious; but the lips of a fool will swallow up himself. ▼
▼ gracious: Heb. grace

verses.text_plain: The beginning of the words of his mouth is foolishness: and the end of his talk is mischievous madness.
verses.verse_html:
13The beginning of the words of his mouth is foolishness: and the end of his talk is mischievous madness. ▼
▼ his talk: Heb. his mouth

footnotes.body_html: ▼ his talk: Heb. his mouth

verses.text_plain: A fool also is full of words: a man cannot tell what shall be; and what shall be after him, who can tell him?
verses.verse_html:
14A fool also is full of words: a man cannot tell what shall be; and what shall be after him, who can tell him? ▼
▼ is full…: Heb. multiplieth words

tokens.text: what shall be; and what shall be after

footnotes.body_html: ▼ is full…: Heb. multiplieth words

verses.text_plain: The labour of the foolish wearieth every one of them, because he knoweth not how to go to the city.
verses.verse_html: 15The labour of the foolish wearieth every one of them, because he knoweth not how to go to the city.

tokens.text: every one of them, because he knoweth

verses.text_plain: Woe to thee, O land, when thy king is a child, and thy princes eat in the morning!
verses.verse_html: 16Woe to thee, O land, when thy king is a child, and thy princes eat in the morning!

verses.text_plain: Blessed art thou, O land, when thy king is the son of nobles, and thy princes eat in due season, for strength, and not for drunkenness!
verses.verse_html: 17Blessed art thou, O land, when thy king is the son of nobles, and thy princes eat in due season, for strength, and not for drunkenness!

verses.text_plain: By much slothfulness the building decayeth; and through idleness of the hands the house droppeth through.
verses.verse_html: 18By much slothfulness the building decayeth; and through idleness of the hands the house droppeth through.

verses.text_plain: A feast is made for laughter, and wine maketh merry: but money answereth all things.
verses.verse_html:
19A feast is made for laughter, and wine maketh merry: but money answereth all things. ▼
▼ maketh…: Heb. maketh glad the life

footnotes.body_text: ▼ maketh…: Heb. maketh glad the life
footnotes.body_html: ▼ maketh…: Heb. maketh glad the life

verses.text_plain: Curse not the king, no not in thy thought; and curse not the rich in thy bedchamber: for a bird of the air shall carry the voice, and that which hath wings shall tell the matter.
verses.verse_html:
20Curse not the king, no not in thy thought; and curse not the rich in thy bedchamber: for a bird of the air shall carry the voice, and that which hath wings shall tell the matter. ▼
▼ thought: or, conscience
